          <p style="color: var(--slate-500); margin-top: 10px; font-size: 0.85rem; line-height: 1.6;">Pawnee County bail bond costs depend on the charge and bail amount set by the judge. Common bail amounts include approximately $500-$1,500 for misdemeanor DUI, $500-$5,000 for most misdemeanors, and $5,000-$50,000+ for felony charges. You pay a percentage of the total bail amount as the premium. Angel Bail Bonds accepts cash, Visa, Mastercard, Zelle, Venmo, and offers financing.</p>
