          <summary style="font-weight: 600; font-size: 0.9rem; color: var(--slate-800);">How long does it take to get released from Pawnee County Jail?</summary>
          <p style="color: var(--slate-500); margin-top: 10px; font-size: 0.85rem; line-height: 1.6;">Most releases from Pawnee County Jail take 1-4 hours after the bail bond is posted, depending on the time of day and how busy the facility is. Pawnee County Jail has a capacity of 51 inmates and processes about 1,235 bookings per year. Angel Bail Bonds can begin the bond process over the phone before arriving at the jail to speed up release.</p>
